# Rescoping Playbook

A short, mirrored version of this lives as a **user-level rule** ("ACCAdminsuite rescoping playbook") so it's available automatically in any brand-new repo without needing to be copied in. Keep both in sync when you learn something new â€” update the user-level rule for process/checklist changes, and add a new case-study entry below for project-specific specifics.

## Why this exists

ACCAdminsuite's core (offline-first, single-file, `.accdata`, IndexedDB blob storage, local launcher bridge, Outlook-sync ingestion, save/load, audit log, theme/UI kit) is proven and hospital-approved. Repeating coworkers/roles (a different admin, the boss, etc.) need narrower tools that share this DNA but cut irrelevant modules and add role-specific ones. Don't rebuild the plumbing each time; don't force every role into one bloated app either.

## Process

1. **Capture the job scope as a conversation, not a spec.** Let the coworker describe their day-to-day in their own words (chasing things up, billing, what triggers each step, what they email/receive). Don't ask them to fill in a schema up front.
2. **Parse notes into a draft plan yourself; fill gaps from what ACCAdminsuite already solved.** Only surface true open questions back to the requester â€” things that would change the shape of the plan, not every field. State your assumptions and defaults explicitly so they're easy to correct.
3. **Decide the reuse strategy** (ask if genuinely ambiguous, otherwise default):
   - **Default: new standalone repo**, scaffolded by copying/forking reusable pieces from ACCAdminsuite (see building blocks below). Each persona gets an independently deployable, independently versioned app â€” safest, matches "we'll do this a few more times."
   - Only propose extracting a **shared core library** once there are 3+ forked suites and a clear, stable common surface â€” premature abstraction before that point costs more than it saves.
   - Adding a module to the *existing* ACCAdminsuite repo is rarely right when the persona's job scope is meaningfully different (couples unrelated products, mixes unrelated users' data/concerns).
4. **Map the new domain onto existing primitives** before inventing new ones. Common translations:
   - Any "thing tracked per person" â†’ `Patient`-like record + a domain entity (`Claim`, `EquipmentLoan`, etc.) referencing it by id.
   - Any "editable rates/prices the org updates over time" â†’ the `serviceRates: Record<Code, number>` pattern in `Settings` (see [src/types/index.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/types/index.ts)) â€” one editable table, versionless, no fixed reset default.
   - Any "attach a file to a record" â†’ `ClaimDocument`-style metadata row + IndexedDB blob store, never bytes in the main autosaved blob (see [src/lib/idb.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/lib/idb.ts), [src/lib/letterCache.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/lib/letterCache.ts)).
   - Any "multi-step status per record" â†’ a small ordered stage enum + a visual step-tracker component, denormalized onto the record for fast list rendering (avoid recomputing status from history on every render).
   - Any "emails start/drive the process" â†’ the staging/Review Queue pattern ([src/lib/staging.ts](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/lib/staging.ts), [src/modules/ReviewQueue.tsx](/Users/prakritichhetri/ACCAdminsuite/src/modules/ReviewQueue.tsx)): land in a queue for one-button accept-into-record, full email history kept per record afterward. Reuse the Outlook-sync + local launcher bridge for automated ingestion once the manual flow is validated â€” don't port the PowerShell bridge on day one of a new repo.
   - Any "generate/track a specific known form" (e.g. ACC4249 loan form) â†’ treat as a document kind + a tracked progress stage first; only build bespoke parsing/extraction once you have a real sample of the form and see it recurring.
5. **Build order:** data model â†’ core record CRUD module â†’ domain-specific centerpiece feature (the thing that makes this persona's job easier day one) â†’ secondary features â†’ polish/UI passes. Don't front-load polish.
6. **Cut aggressively.** Anything specific to the *other* persona's workflow (e.g. nursing service-code billing, compliance rules, complex-case tracking) should not exist in the new repo at all, not just be hidden in the UI.
7. **After shipping, log a case study below** so the next rescoping (next coworker, or the boss) starts from real examples instead of a blank playbook.

## Building blocks worth reusing as-is (from ACCAdminsuite)

- Persistence: `src/lib/idb.ts` (IndexedDB stores, blob storage, recent-files), `src/state/store.ts` (Zustand store, autosave, save-into-file-handle, rollback-on-commit-failure pattern).
- File handling: `src/lib/fileSniff.ts` (byte-level type detection), `src/components/PdfPreview.tsx` (offline preview + text fallback), `src/lib/letterCache.ts` (MIME inference, blob/parse caching).
- UI shell: `src/components/TopBar.tsx`, `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `src/lib/theme.ts`, `src/index.css` (theme tokens, density modes).
- Ingestion pipeline (only once manual flow is proven): `scripts/launcher/*.ps1` (local bridge, Outlook COM sync, folder watch), `src/lib/localAccBridge.ts`, `src/lib/staging.ts`, `src/modules/ReviewQueue.tsx`.
- Build/verify tooling: `scripts/verify-build.mjs` (CSP checks â€” keep `connect-src 'self'` for the local bridge, `'wasm-unsafe-eval'` if OCR is needed), `scripts/copy-launcher.mjs`.

## Case studies

### 1. Loan Equipment Tracker (coworker, started 2026-07-11)

- **Persona:** Coworker with similar role to the primary user, but scoped to hospital loan equipment (not nursing service billing).
- **Job scope (coworker's own words):** track patient info useful for chasing up loan equipment and billing; know where each patient is in the process and who needs following up/re-emailing; maintain an editable equipment price list; save the initial patient email plus all subsequent emails as attachments under each patient for full history; a visual progress tracker per patient; the ACC4249 loan form is the essential first step many patients skip.
- **Reuse strategy chosen:** new standalone repo, forked from ACCAdminsuite, reusing persistence/UI/file-handling building blocks above; email ingestion starts manual (attach email/attachment per patient), Outlook-sync/launcher bridge ported later once validated.
- **Kept:** `Patient` record shape (id/name/nhi/dob/notes), IndexedDB blob + document metadata pattern, editable-rates-table pattern (repurposed as the price list), save/load `.accdata`, audit log, theme/UI kit.
- **Cut:** `ServiceLine`/`ServiceCode` package calculator, `Approval` (NS04/NS05), `Billing`/`InvoiceLine` nursing-specific flow, `ComplexCases`, `Declines`, `Compliance` module, `ImportedTables`.
- **New:** `EquipmentLoan`/loan-case entity per patient, `PriceListItem` catalog, ordered progress-stage enum + step-tracker UI, per-patient email/attachment history view, ACC4249 tracked as a document-kind + stage (bespoke parsing deferred â€” no sample form captured yet).
- **Open questions logged for follow-up:** exact ordered list of progress stages (drafted from the one sample follow-up email + "loan form is step one", needs coworker confirmation); billing model for equipment (flat fee vs. per-item price vs. daily rate); whether billing target is ACC or the DHB; whether the Outlook-sync bridge should be pointed at the coworker's own mailbox/shared inbox and on what timeline.
- **Lessons for next time:** ask for the actual sample form/attachment up front rather than assuming it's included with an email; the "cut down current suite" framing usually means a fully separate persona-specific product, not an added module for someone who also needs the original features.

### 2. Manager Remittance / Task Tracker (Amy, the manager â€” started 2026-07-12)

- **Persona:** Amy May, the team manager. Oversees invoicing across ~25 ACC contracts owned by different team members; wants to reconcile ACC remittances against invoices and delegate the held/declined lines to whoever owns each contract, then track progress. SHARED across manager + team (multi-user), not single-user. Repo: `/Users/prakritichhetri/ACC-RemittanceTracker`.
- **Job scope (own words):** dashboard of invoicing across all contracts; upload invoicing + remittances; cross-check them, drop already-paid patients (or note paid), surface still-held ones with the reason code; send review items to the team member responsible for the contract; track task progress. Explicitly NOT a monthly-billing entry tool.
- **Reuse strategy:** new standalone repo **forked from ACC-LoanEquipmentTracker** (nearest sibling, leaner shell than ACCAdminsuite). Stripped all loan/equipment/email/monitoring/PDF/OCR code.
- **Kept:** offline-first `.accdata` + IndexedDB persistence, Zustand store skeleton (autosave, lock/idle, recovery, recent files, ZIP backup), theme/UI kit, `AssumptionBanner`, launcher loopback server + `verify-build`/`copy-launcher`, the "raw upload blob + metadata row + re-parse/backfill" pattern.
- **Cut:** `Patient`/`EquipmentLoan`, price list, all email/staging/Outlook-COM ingestion, PDF preview + Tesseract OCR (+ their deps and the CSP `wasm-unsafe-eval`/`blob:` directives), monitoring import.
- **New:** `Contract`/`TeamMember`(role manager|staff)/`InvoiceBatch`+`InvoiceLine`/`RemittanceBatch`+`RemittanceLine`/`ReviewTask`(+append-only `TaskNote[]`)/`SourceFileMeta`, all with `updatedAt`/`updatedBy`; seed catalogue from the real annual-billing workbook tabs (stable `contract_<slug>` ids, expired = inactive); CSV importers grounded in real samples; `REASON_CODES` lookup; pure `reconcile.ts` + a `reconcileData` store step that auto-creates one review task per held line, auto-assigned to the contract owner and preserving human edits across re-parse; Dashboard/Invoices/Remittances/Review Queue/My Tasks/Contracts/Team/Settings modules; one generic `DismissableAssumption` for all banners; **shared-folder sync** (`src/lib/sync.ts` LWW-per-record merge + notes union; launcher extended with opt-in `sync-config.json` + `/_acc/sync` + `/_acc/sync/status`). Browser only calls its own loopback bridge (keeps `connect-src 'self'`); the launcher merges the incoming payload with a SINGLE shared state file on the network drive (I:) that every machine points at â€” no host PC, no TCP listener, no port, no firewall rule, just the same watch-a-shared-location file-share I/O as the sibling suites' folder-watch. Sync config/state are git-ignored (PHI).
- **Critical data finding:** the invoice `ClaimNumber` matches the remittance **`ACC45 Ref`** column, NOT the long numeric `ACC Claim Number`; client names disagree between the two files for the same claim â€” so matching is claim-only, names are display-only. Deterministic per-batch line ids keep review tasks linked across re-parse.
- **Lessons for next time:** fork from the nearest sibling suite, not always ACCAdminsuite; when a whole capability is deleted (PDF/OCR), also tighten the CSP and drop the now-unused deps + build steps + their `verify-build` assertions or the build breaks; `launch.ps1` must stay ASCII-only (no em-dashes â€” `copy-launcher.mjs` asserts it); a partial `node_modules` from a repo copy can leave dev packages missing their `dist/` (clean reinstall fixes it); for multi-user-on-a-network-drive, DEFAULT TO a shared-file merge (every machine reads/merges/writes the SAME file on the drive, atomically via temp-then-move) over a host+LAN-listener design â€” a hospital network will reliably let you read/write a mapped drive but may well block a new inbound port, and the shared-file design is also simpler (no host/client asymmetry) and reuses a pattern (watch a shared location) already proven by the sibling suites' folder-watch. The explicit LWW+notes-union merge itself (not the transport) is what's worth keeping â€” it's simpler/more testable than a CRDT and transport-agnostic, so this pivot only touched the launcher + Settings + a couple of type names, not the merge logic.

### 3. Porting reconciliation LOGIC back into ACCAdminsuite itself (billing/remittance import, started 2026-07-12)

- **Not a rescoping** â€” this is the reverse direction: porting mature *logic* from a sibling suite (case study #2's `ACC-RemittanceTracker`) into ACCAdminsuite's own long-stalled `Billing.tsx`, which had never grown past a manual CRUD ledger despite an `invoiceSheet` field hinting an importer was always intended. Confirms the sibling-suite pattern is bidirectional: a suite built for a narrower persona can mature a piece of domain logic (CSV/XLSX parsing, claim-matching, reason codes) fast enough that porting it BACK to the original suite is the efficient path, rather than re-deriving it there from scratch.
- **What ported cleanly, unchanged:** `reasonCodes.ts` (ACC's own documented codes â€” not suite-specific at all); the ACC45-Ref-vs-ACC-Claim-Number claim-matching rule and the "declined lines are often free-text only, no code" finding; the remittance block-parser's two hard-won bug fixes (a free-text comment containing "claim"/"paid" words must not be misdetected as a new header block; a short undelimited trailing footnote row must not be parsed as a data row).
- **What got adapted, not copied verbatim:** the whole `Contract`/`TeamMember` ownership + `ReviewTask` delegation layer was skipped entirely â€” ACCAdminsuite is single-user, so "who does this held line get assigned to" doesn't exist; a match simply updates the existing `InvoiceLine` in place (`needsReview`/`heldReasonCode`/`heldReason` fields added to it) instead of spawning a separate `RemittanceLine` + task record. The xlsx adapter was NOT ported: the source suite hand-rolled a JSZip+regex XML reader specifically to avoid a heavy dependency, but ACCAdminsuite already uses `ExcelJS` for its own export/import (`lib/excel.ts`/`lib/excelImport.ts`), so re-using that established convention was strictly better than introducing a second, redundant xlsx-parsing code path.
- **Real-file-shape reality check paid off again:** the source suite's samples had ONE claimant-name column and a generic "Service Code" header; the real ACC monthly invoice-schedule exports (`ONNMAR26.xlsx` etc., read for header shape only, no rows committed) split the name across 4 columns (`ClaimantFirstName/SecondName/ThirdName/Surname`) and use `ACCServiceItemCode1` for the billed code, with typed `Date` cells (not date-strings) for every date column. The importer tries the real-shape headers first and falls back to the source suite's generic aliases (`ClientName`/`ServiceCode`/`Amount`), so both a genuine ACC export and a hand-written CSV import correctly. There is no ACC45/PO-number column in the invoice schedule at all â€” left blank on import rather than guessed, since ACCAdminsuite already fills those from Approvals separately.
- **Lessons for next time:** before porting a parser, check whether the target repo already has an equivalent library dependency (ExcelJS here) â€” matching the TARGET's existing convention beats a literal port of the SOURCE's implementation choice; always re-verify a "confirmed" source-suite column assumption (single name column, generic service-code header) against the target's OWN real sample files before trusting it, because two suites pulling from the "same" ACC export can still see genuinely different column layouts if they're different report types (schedule vs. remittance) or different regions/contracts.

### 4. Reverse-port from Loan Equipment Tracker â†’ ACCAdminsuite (useful UX/lifecycle, 2026-07-14)

- **Not a rescoping** â€” Loan Eq matured quiet launcher, tab-close shutdown, Accept undo, remittance Remove, attention badges, Billing tabs, typography, assumption banners, Help FAQ, Mail Reference, and I-drive `_Staging` writeback; Phase 1 of the cross-suite plan brought the overlapping pieces back into Admin on `main`.
- **Shipped on `main`:** Wave A `da70246`; Wave B `8b2c307`; Wave C `a67ef5e`.
- **What ported (adapted):** quiet `.vbs` + `-Quiet` Hidden starts (suite dir stays `%USERPROFILE%\ACC-Suite`); `launcherLifecycle.ts` + `lifecycle.ps1` heartbeat/goodbye; typography tokens; `AssumptionBanner` + Admin-specific banners (ACC Inbox filters, remittance stale days, I-drive staging); Help Center with Admin FAQs; HRQ Accept undo toast + `undoHrqAccept`; remittance batch Remove + invoice re-reconcile; labelled sidebar badges + attention row pin/tint; Billing Invoices / Needs review / Imports tabs + list pagination; Mail Reference module (sheet defaults already include District Nursing handoffs); Admin I-drive path grammar `Letters\year\month\{LAST, First} CLAIM\` under `_Staging` (not Enable/Ramps).
- **What was deliberately not copied:** Enable/Ramps filing, loan stages, monitoring workbook, price-list draft, pale-green Enable checklist content, remittance PDF invent, email mutation undo.
- **RQ cherry-picks:** Admin already had search + byte-identical discard + HRQ SLA/auto-accept â€” those stayed; only Accept undo + optional I-drive staging checkbox were added on Accept.
- **Docs:** Admin `docs/PENDING-TASKS.md` lists what was inherited; Remittance Phase 2 shipped as `15d9c48`; Loan Eq `docs/PENDING-TASKS.md` Â§7 marked Done (Phase 3).
- **Lessons:** reverse-ports should rebuild path grammar for the target persona (Admin Letters tree vs Loan Eq Enable/Ramps); remittance Remove needs batch+payment application records even when the original Admin import only mutated invoice lines in place.
